<item>
            <title>[SEC-1628] add authentication-success-handler to &lt;remember-me&gt; tag</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1628</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are using an AuthenticationSuccessHandler to post-process login information to cache attributes into the HttpSession (we&apos;re using a third-party servlet that can handle some database queries by itself but needs the appropriate keys, etc.).  However, after a remember-me login, there is no way to insert a success handler to perform the appropriate initialization for the new session.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be helpful to have an authentication-success-handler-ref attribute on the &amp;lt;remember-me&amp;gt; tag analogous to the attribute on the &amp;lt;*-login&amp;gt; tags, triggered after the RememberMeServices handles a persistent login.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(The forum link is not my post, but there appears to be a significant desire for this feature.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
